snippet.title: Lisa Monique Beauty
snippet.description:
As a 55 year old beauty enthusiast, I want to help other mature women navigate the world of beauty and fashion, finding the best products for our ever changing faces and bodies.  Mature women have different beauty needs than what is shown by the majority of beauty influencers. Please subscribe and join me on this journey to discover the best products and practices as I try and test new (and old) products and give you my unbiased opinions on how they work on my more mature skin.

About Me:  Wife, Mother, Photographer, Military Veteran, Empty Nester, Travel Lover, Beauty Enthusiast.  Please follow me on Instagram for live stories and topics that may not be published here.  @lisamoniquebeauty

Brazilian/British in Wales (UK) | Motherhood, Beauty & Lifestyle | Creator of #MindfulMotherhood

Hi,  I'm Ysis Lorenna, I moved from Brazil to the UK in 2009 and I live in South Wales with my Brazilian-British family.

I've been blogging & vlogging since 2011, and a few years into my new role as a mum, in 2018, I started #MindfulMotherhood out of my own need to better understand my parenting choices and be more intentional in raising my kids. The series offers mothers a positive place to pause & reflect more deeply on parenting, learn techniques & share personal experiences of how to turn off the auto-pilot and be more conscious as a parent, letting go of the overwhelming, multitasking, always busy ideal way of living in today's society.

I also share tips & tricks on how to become fluent in English, based on my own experience of learning English as a second language.

snippet.title: Lexi Jong
snippet.description:
I am a 40-year-old former educator and makeup enthusiast. I love discovering the subtle nuances that exist between formulas, shades, and so forth. If you are like me, you have had some makeup regrets in the past - either from missing out on something you still can't stop thinking about or from giving in to the hype and buying something that you don't love. My goal is to provide information on luxury beauty products to help prevent these regrets so you can curate a collection that you truly love. 

I am always on top of the latest sales and new releases to keep you informed. I post everything on Shoplist and recommend bookmarking this page and checking it regularly: https://shoplist.us/lexijong

Follow me on Instagram @alexisjong
https://www.instagram.com/alexisjong/
and on Tik Tok https://www.tiktok.com/@lexijong

snippet.title: Everyday Edit
snippet.description: Beauty through the lens of Continuous Improvement. Making wise purchases, with purpose and intent. We all work hard for our money and should only invest in the best performing products. As new technology and innovation arise, I integrate and "study" them with specific goals in mind associated with their given claims. I collect data and make decisions about keeping or discarding products based on how well they meet goals. Plus, I love cosmetics! So this is a labor of love and personal research with the ultimate goal of curating a final cut (although it will probably never be final) of outstanding quality products that deliver. I hope that my experiences can help to inform your future purchases.

snippet.title: Shrimpy McGee
snippet.description:
Hi! I'm Helen! I share everything I know about WOMEN'S HAIR LOSS and REGROWTH, ROGAINE AND MINOXIDIL, and HAIR PROBLEMS. Shampoo and scalp product reviews, too: Olaplex, Viviscal, Kerastase, Invati and The Ordinary Hair Serum. I also dabble in helper/alternative hair, intuitive eating and ending restrictive eating and food!

New videos every week! SUBSCRIBE HERE:  https://bit.ly/2JykTR4 

I've stopped using Patreon but...

If you would like to donate $5 to my channel to help support what I do, here's the PayPal link! https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&hosted_button_id=BE2PS9PS3G2F6&source=url

More about me: I'm a writer and editor (and a mom) in my 40s.  Shrimpy McGee is my channel for these hair vids (especially dealing with using Rogaine and minoxidil) plus beauty and makeup videos. I also do other fun stuff, like work and jobs, and intuitive eating). I'm based in Toronto.

snippet.title: H2O Oxygen Fashion

H2O, Oxygen, Fashion: The basic needs of a FASHIONISTA.  


H2O, Oxygen, Fashion, are the basic survival needs of a true FASHIONISTA.  The H2O-Oxygen-Fashion Channel strives to fulfill your fashion needs by bringing you the latest and hottest trends in fashion, how to style and wear them, and where to buy them. 

Fashion is not just about the clothes.  It's beauty (hair, nails, make-up), & styling (how you wear it and accessorizing). 

SUBSCRIBE to H2O-Oxygen-Fashion to get more videos on fashion, Beauty, Styling, How-to and Tips & Tricks of the Fashion Industry.  We aim to upload videos weekly, sometimes daily to keep you in the know.
